## Netlify Security Headers - Lighthouse Best Practices Optimized
/*
  X-Frame-Options: SAMEORIGIN
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  X-XSS-Protection: 1; mode=block
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), microphone=(), camera=(), payment=(), usb=(), magnetometer=(), gyroscope=(), speaker=()
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' blob:; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; font-src 'self' https://fonts.gstatic.com; img-src 'self' https://images.pexels.com data: blob:; connect-src 'self' https://*.netlify.app; frame-ancestors 'self'; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self' https://*.netlify.app; upgrade-insecure-requests;
  Strict-Transport-Security: max-age=31536000; includeSubDomains

/sw.js
  Cache-Control: no-cache
  Service-Worker-Allowed: /

/*.css
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/*.js
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
